# 3D Card Effect — Exebenus Style

## What Already Works (DO NOT BREAK)
The `TrendingCardScroll.tsx` component already implements:
- ✅ Scroll-pinned sticky section with dark `.tcard-bg` background
- ✅ Real Charizard Base Set card image from `images.pokemontcg.io/base1/4_hires.png`
- ✅ Framer Motion scroll-driven rotation (rotateY, rotateX, scale via `useScroll`)
- ✅ Two perspective ground lines (`.tcard-line .l1` and `.l2`)
- ✅ Conic-gradient rotating rings (`.tcard-rings`)
- ✅ Floating spark particles (`.tcard-spark`)
- ✅ Stats panel that fades in on scroll with animated stat bars
- ✅ Card reflection below the card
- ✅ Reduced motion fallback

## Enhancements Needed (CSS ONLY in globals.css)

### 1. Stage Lines — Add Teal Glow
`.tcard-line` needs Exebenus-style teal (#2CA6A4) glow:
```css
.tcard-line {
  /* existing styles + add: */
  box-shadow: 0 0 12px rgba(44,166,164,0.5), 0 0 28px rgba(44,166,164,0.25);
  filter: blur(0.3px);
}
```

### 2. Card Container — Teal Outer Glow
`.tcard-3d` box-shadow needs teal glow mixed in:
```css
.tcard-3d {
  box-shadow:
    0 40px 90px -30px rgba(0,0,0,0.8),
    0 0 0 1px rgba(255,255,255,0.05) inset,
    0 0 50px -6px rgba(44,166,164,0.45),  /* teal glow */
    0 0 80px -10px rgba(58,111,245,0.35);  /* blue glow */
}
```

### 3. Rings — Incorporate Teal
`.tcard-rings` conic-gradient should include teal:
```css
background: conic-gradient(from 0deg,
  rgba(44,166,164,0),
  rgba(44,166,164,0.55),
  rgba(58,111,245,0.55),
  rgba(238,21,21,0.55),
  rgba(255,203,5,0.55),
  rgba(44,166,164,0)
);
```

### 4. Background Contrast
`.tcard-bg` — ensure very deep dark for maximum card pop:
```css
background: linear-gradient(180deg, #050810 0%, #0a1225 58%, #040608 100%);
```

### 5. Hero Card (page.tsx hero section)
The `.hero-card` in the main hero should:
- Use dark background instead of white
- Have colored glow shadow
- Consider replacing the sprite-based card with a real card image
- Add mouse-reactive tilt via JavaScript

## DO NOT change the Framer Motion logic in TrendingCardScroll.tsx
Only enhance through CSS in globals.css.
